  "title": "Electrical Technical Programme Manager",
  "description": "<h3>Role Purpose<br /></h3><p>We are seeking an experienced Electrical Technical Programme Manager (TPM) to lead the development and delivery of next-generation electrical system products for data centre projects. The role</p><p>combines technical expertise with programme management to oversee the full lifecycle of design,</p><p>implementation, and commissioning.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p>• Support the development of next-generation electrical systems and infrastructure.</p><p>• Collaborate with engineering teams to integrate new technologies into product development.</p><p>• Produce system-level concepts, schematic designs, and detailed electrical documentation.</p><p>• Lead cross-functional stakeholders (design, construction, facilities, and EHS) on programme-level</p><p>deliverables and commissioning activities.</p><p>• Manage external vendors providing design and construction services across the product lifecycle.</p><p>• Prepare and maintain technical documentation, including statements of work, engineering reports,</p><p>design documents, cost analyses, budgets, schedules, and commissioning plans.</p><p>• Coordinate and consolidate design documentation across all disciplines for large-scale data centre</p><p>builds.</p><p>• Review design drawings and Autodesk Revit models, ensuring accuracy, milestone compliance,</p><p>and resolution of critical coordination issues.</p><p>• Develop proprietary electrical design standards and data centre products.</p><p>• Implement automation tools and workflows to streamline production and reduce design cycle</p><p>times.</p><p>• Identify and escalate technical and programme issues, develop solutions, and drive approved</p><p>actions to completion.<br /></p><h3>Qualifications</h3><p>• Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Electrical Engineering or a related field.</p><p>• Proven experience in programme management within electrical systems, infrastructure, or large-</p><p>scale construction (data centre experience strongly preferred).</p><p>• Strong understanding of electrical system design, commissioning, and operations.</p><p>• Proficiency with Autodesk Revit and design review processes.</p><p>• Demonstrated ability to manage multiple vendors and complex cross-functional programmes.</p><p>• Excellent leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills.</p><p>• Experience developing proprietary standards or working within fast-paced product development</p><p>environments is advantageous.</p>",
